We love achari gobi....original recipe said achari aloo ....we just made gobi using the same recipe ....a favourite at home....shall try Paneer next time

My interest in Paneer, has increased over the last 4 months. After I discovered Punjab-Sindh Paneer. The shop was one of the few that was open during the lock down and was conveniently located for me to pick up stuff, without waiting in queue. This was a recipe I came across recently and made for Tuesday lunch. 
Achari Paneer Pulao. Simple (actually all the recipes I chose are simple ) and delicious. I am partial to ‘achari’ flavours.....so loved it! #lockdowndiaries #acharipaneerpulao #paneerrecipes #onepanmeal

"CRONACHE DALLA PANDEMIA" di ERICA MANNA (ebook) IL CANNETO EDITORE 2020

Forse solo ora si comincia a intuire cosa abbia significato (e a quali conseguenze abbia portato) per tanti cittadini il lockdown. Questa raccolta di storie genovesi a firma della giornalista di @larepubblica Erica Manna @ibianconiglia, che per il momento trovate solo nella versione digitale, ci apre la strada alla sua comprensione. La bella foto in copertina  di Giorgio Salvadori, di cui presto pubblicheremo un intero catalogo illustrato sempre a tema "quarantena". NEW ARTICLE! Common Sense. We all have it, and surely that’s enough to curb the spread of a global virus?

Contributor @eve_willis , 22, writes about the UK Government’s reliance on common sense and why it’s both wrong and unfair. 

She writes: “is it fair to rely on this so-called public consciousness to capably and rigorously stamp out the virus? Or is it asking too much of a population already fractured by underlying structural inequalities, exacerbated by years of austerity?”

Read the full short piece at TwentysomethingNews.com [Link in Bio]

node.text:
#BeetrootPotatoCutlets

Ingrediants
1. Beetroot/carrot
2. Potato
3. Breadcrumbs
4. Cornflour
5. Salt, cardomom, ginger galic chilli paste,  Chaat Masaala, salt as per taste, Crushed Cumin seed, Fennel seeds

1. Take 2 Potatoes, Boil them in water with  a pinch of salt, Once boiled mash the potatoes.

2. Add grated Beetroot, Carrot, Boiled Peas to the mashed potatoes

3. Add Ginger-Garlic-Chilli paste, 1 tbsp of Chaat Masaala, salt as per taste, Crushed Cumin seed, Fennel seeds to the mixture.

4. Add coriander leaves,1 tsp of dried breadcrumbs and 1 tsp of cornflour

5. Mix everything together, Make cutlet like shapes.
Heat the Oil in the pan, Shallow fry the cutlets till cooked evenly.

** Enjoy this tasty recipe with mint chutney/Tomato Ketchup.

I broke down in tears!
?
To the world, it was a rented place, a temporary address. To me, it was my house.
?
I moved to Mumbai before four years. Once I rented a house, I started buying my own stuff.
?
It started with replacing my phone, then laptop and then buying a nice ride. Furniture followed and lastly, I made the kitchen functional.
?
It was indeed a home to me. I had to vacate it last Friday, given the times we are in.
?
As I sat on floor on Friday evening in this hall room, which was now empty, I broke down.
?
All the hard-work of previous four years suddenly vanished.
?
My Mom summed it up beautifully in one statement and I believe she is right:
?
'You'll build a better house.'
?
For now, I have moved back to my hometown - Ahmedabad. Mindset at present - let's see what future holds.
?
#Mumbai #LockdownDiaries #Home

If everything goes well we should have another 7 full days to go in our lockdown coop. It’s a strange feeling. Honestly, it feels like we just arrived and at the same time, it feels like we have always lived in 2 rooms without ever going outside!

The highlights for today were numerous. We first had the pleasure to receive a package from my darling mum-in-law with many books for ?????? and a “bug bingo” which we have played for hours today. By the time we are allowed to leave the room we will be experts in bugs!!!!
We spent a good part of the day doing some homework while ??‍??was working. 
Once all the work was done for the day, we all enjoyed a little workout. I’m introducing my loves to Pilates which is fun.
This evening we celebrated my dad’s birthday and the end of our first week inside with a glass of ?and with a delicious chocolate cake (the food we are given is pretty nice, not exactly balanced and healthy, but tonight the dessert was spot on ?)

node.text:
Resharing it as a post because it will be there on my handle forever and I request my followers do choose your area heroes of  lockdown. Who served others during difficult times with a smile on their face??

It won't take much of your time in doing this ?
 
She is my hero 
Why I choose her...
I have been watching her diligently performing her job to deliver food articles as a part of the essential requirements to families and individuals across Navi Mumbai. She is a phenomenal strong woman who literally shows what it means by women empowernment and serving the society. Of course she also takes care of her family being able to have a job and deliver some that she continues to provide .Meet Balpreet Kaur Saini

Sharing @goodwind.mototours 
#heroeswhoride

 
Meet Balpreet Kaur Saini. 
Balpreet works with @zomatoin and has been tirelessly delivering food parcels. Thanks to her and heroes like her, many in Bombay have been able to get their meals at the safety of their homes.

Even in the challenging weather and times, she kept riding for us.

Thanks to Balpreet for her sheer will. For being one of the #HeroesWhoRide

And thanks to Akhtar a.k.a. @winter_wanderer for nominating this hero, and to @zomatoin @mumbaipolice for taking care of heroes like Balpreet.

node.text: As fresh as a daisy. Not quite. A prolonged endometriosis flare has me feeling exhausted at this point in August, but my mind is full of ideas and enthusiasm.
